<materialsCitation id="68983F7FFFC69B177CA4FA2EFA67219E" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3804718302" location="Southeast region" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" specimenCount="1" stateProvince="Western Australia">
<keyLead id="63019617FFC69B177CA4FA2EFA67219E" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">
1. Pronotum evenly, densely punctate. Pronotal pilosity dense, long. Males with pronotal lateral margin with maculation narrow and not full-length, or absent. 
<location id="DD2F63F9FFC69B177E37FA4BFD5E219E" LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:50598434FFC69B177CA4FAE5FA672236:DD2F63F9FFC69B177E37FA4BFD5E219E" box="[516,676,1497,1519]" name="Southeast region" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" stateProvince="Western Australia">Southeast region</location>
of southern 
<collectingRegion id="1A34FBC0FFC69B177F2EFA48FC3D219E" box="[797,967,1497,1519]" country="Australia" name="Western Australia" pageId="5" pageNumber="244">Western Australia</collectingRegion>
......... 
<taxonomicName id="1FF04EA1FFC69B177803FA4BFA67219E" authority="(Rigout &amp; Allard, 1997)" baseAuthorityName="Rigout &amp; Allard" baseAuthorityYear="1997" box="[1072,1437,1497,1519]" class="Insecta" family="Cetoniidae" genus="Diaphonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="244" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bacchusi">
